{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-tsx","path":"/content/1803.03635","result":{"pageContext":{"slug":"/content/1803.03635","markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Pruning can reduce network by 90% without compromising accuracy"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Standard pruning naturally uncovers sub-networks whose initialization made them capable of training effectively"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"They find \"winning tickets\" consistently for MNSIT and CIFAR10"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Formally:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"$$f(x, \\theta)$$ is some dense FF network where $$\\theta_0 \\sim D_\\theta$$ for some distribution of parameters $$D_\\theta$$"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"$$f$$ reaches $$l$$ validation loss and test accuracy $$a$$ at some iteration $$j$$ from e.g. SGD"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Consider training $$f(x, m \\dot \\theta)$$ for some fixed mask $$m \\in {0, 1}^{\\Vert{\\theta}\\Vert}$$\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This will reach some validation loss $l'$, at iteration $j'$ for some test accuracy $a'$"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"LTH States: $$\\exists M$$ where $j' \\leq j$, $a' \\leq a$"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To find such $M$ they propose an algorithm:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ol","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Randomly initialize $f(x, \\theta_0)$"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Train for some fixed iterations"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Prune p% of the network, to construct the mask $M$"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Reset the parameters to $\\theta_0$ and retrain the model"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Repeat this procedure iteratively over n rounds, combining the mask over each round. They should empirically that this out-performs doing this once."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"They have experimental results on MNIST and CIFAR10"}]}],"data":{"quirksMode":false}},"frontmatter":{"date":null,"title":"The Lottery Ticket Hypothesis Finding Sparse, Trainable Neural Networks","state":null,"slug":null,"tags":"paper ml","source":"https://arxiv.org/abs/1803.03635","code":null},"fields":{"slug":"/content/1803.03635"}}}},"staticQueryHa